author: Andrew Nemec | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: Keondre Dew, elite JC SF, visiting Oregon State Beavers basketball this weekend
text:
The Oregon State Beavers already have four-star point guard JaQuori McLaughlin and three-star power forward Ben Kone in the fold for the class of 2016, but still have work to do.
This weekend, Oregon State will host former Rivals three-star small forward Keondre Dew , who had offers from UConn, DePaul, Florida State, Hawaii, Kansas State, Memphis, Oklahoma State, Oregon State, Central Florida and Washington State coming out of high school, the prospect confirmed.
Dew, a 6-foot-8, 220-pound athlete, is currently at City College of San Francisco after originally signing with Tulsa out of Elev8 Sports (Delray Beach, Florida) in the class of 2014.
As a senior, he averaged 17 points, 9 rebounds and 2.5 assists.
"Keondre is a great kid and a hard worker," Cody Toppert, head coach at Elev8 Sports Institute, told the Tulsa World . "He plays with a tremendous energy and tenacity, and he goes hard every single play. You can always count on him to be locked in for the duration of a game."
Oregon State had its best basketball recruiting class in school history in the class of 2015.
So far, the Beavers have been able to carry that momentum into this year's cycle.
